```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Warning: Dark Web Forum Data</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }
        .container {
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            text-align: center;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #ff0000;
            font-size: 2em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        p {
            color: #333;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        input[type="text"] {
            width: 80%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #ff0000;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #cc0000;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Warning: Dark Web Forum Data</h1>
    <p>Some types of data on dark web forums can be extremely valuable, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Personal Identifiable Information (PII)</li>
        <li>Financial Data</li>
        <li>Stolen Credentials</li>
        <li>Sensitive Documents</li>
        <li>Exploits and Vulnerabilities</li>
        <li>Child Exploitation Materials (CEM)</li>
        <li>Phishing Kits</li>
        <li>Malware and Ransomware</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Engaging in activities related to these data types can be highly risky and illegal.</p>
    <form action="#" method="post">
        <label for="socialSecurity">Please enter your social security number to proceed:</label>
        <input type="text" id="socialSecurity" name="socialSecurity" placeholder="Enter your social security number" required>
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

This HTML form includes a styled container with a warning message and a prompt for the user to enter their social security number. The form is designed to look like a warning dialog, and the user must enter their social security number before proceeding.

